<TITLE> Hasina fears for life if treated here: doctor </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 16 (bdnews24.com)Sheikh Hasina is not agreeing to be treated in any hospital in the country as she fears attempts on her life, her doctor said Saturday. Hasina wants treatment abroad, her personal physician Prof ABM Abdullah told bdnews24.com after examining the former prime minister Saturday. Prof Abdullah visited Hasina in the special jail, set up on the Sangsad Bhaban premises, at the request of prison authorities. He said he spent almost two hours from 10.00 am examining Sheikh Hasina's physical condition. Asked when Hasina would be shifted to a hospital, the doctor told bdnews24.com: "She is afraid of taking treatment in any hospital here." Proper treatment for her ear complaint is not possible in the country, he added. Asked why the AL president was afraid of taking treatment in any hospital in the country, he replied: "She is afraid of an attempt on her life." On Hasina's ailments, Prof Abdullah said: "She is suffering from allergies. She is still very weak." "However, her blood pressure is now under control to some extent. She had a good sleep last night." The personal physician said that during his visit Saturday, unlike on previous occasions, neither the inspector general nor deputy inspector general of prisons was present.. bdnews
